        <div class="course-content-block" data-aos="fade-up">
          <h2>About the Program</h2>
          <p>
            The Auxiliary Nursing & Midwifery (A.N.M.) diploma is a two-year
            program that trains students as frontline healthcare workers in
            community health, primary care and maternal and child health services.
          </p>
          <p>
            ANM graduates play a critical role in rural and semi-urban healthcare
            delivery, working as health workers, community nurses and midwives
            within the public health system.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="course-content-block" data-aos="fade-up">
          <h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2>
          <ul class="course-list">
            <li>Passed 10+2 or equivalent from a recognised board</li>
            <li>Minimum age of 17 years as on 31st December of admission year</li>
            <li>Must have passed English as a subject</li>
            <li>Medically fit as per Gujarat Nursing Council norms</li>
            <li>Female candidates only (as per INC / GNC norms)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="course-content-block" data-aos="fade-up">
